<div class="tips-box">
  <h3>Tips and Tricks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>☝️ Make sure to do the proofing phase of teaching a skill, it's mandatory to being up the difficulty after they've shown that they can do it in a controlled environment.</li>
    <li>☝️ Start with a few different contexts. After 1 session, mark something new. Just try not to rush past those 3 criteria too fast.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="info-box">
  <p>This is another lesson where the key is <strong>not to rush</strong>. You don't need to skip ahead here.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Phase 1: Perform the Action.</strong> Only when they love to do the action move past with confidence.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 2: Pair the Action.</strong> Only when they go right onto the platform when you say "Place" can you move on to Phase 3.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 3: Proof the Action.</strong> This takes the longest. Proof in as many different contexts as you can. Don't skip it and then go to next lesson.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

